 {"id":"bd-yx9r.13","title":"Combinator, service, transport, remote, and spork parity","description":"Upstream asupersync exports high-level orchestration families that sit on top of runtime/networking foundations: combinators, service layers, transport adapters, remote helpers, link/session surfaces, and spork-style execution tools. ANSI C currently lacks most of this public orchestration layer.","design":"This epic should make the C port feel like a usable async framework rather than only a kernel plus scattered protocol pieces.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Higher-level orchestration surfaces exist with explicit cancellation/outcome behavior.\\nB. Tests cover composition semantics, buffering/rate limits/timeouts/retries, and failure propagation.\\nC. Protocol/application layers can build on these APIs instead of inventing ad hoc wrappers.","notes":"Primary upstream references: combinator exports in src/lib.rs, src/service/*, src/transport/*, remote-related exports, src/spork, src/link.rs, and session-related surfaces.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:14.287586776Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T20:42:40.382725357Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T20:42:40.379473997Z","close_reason":"Superseded by earlier canonical reopened parity backlog issues under bd-yx9r.7 through bd-yx9r.12","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["combinator","crate-parity","service","transport"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.13","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:14.287586776Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.13.1","title":"Port join/race/select/timeout/retry combinator surface","description":"ANSI C needs the real user-facing combinator layer promised by the upstream crate, not just ad hoc kernel helpers. This includes joins, races, selection, timeout wrappers, retry-ish composition, and explicit outcome aggregation semantics.","design":"Implement the combinators as stable public APIs with strong cancellation and ownership contracts, backed by law-style tests and realistic composition scenarios.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public combinator APIs exist and integrate with Outcome, cancellation, and scope rules.\\nB. Unit/property tests cover algebraic composition and loser-drain behavior.\\nC. Smoke scenarios demonstrate real multi-branch orchestration with detailed logs.","notes":"Depends on B and D.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:17.469048894Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T20:42:30.818613228Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T20:42:30.818022487Z","close_reason":"Superseded by earlier canonical reopened parity backlog issues under bd-yx9r.7 through bd-yx9r.12","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["combinator","crate-parity"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.13.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.13","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:17.469048894Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}

